WEBVTT

00:00.129 --> 00:02.679
_

00:03.972 --> 00:07.975
1836 Republic of Texas

00:07.976 --> 00:11.611
The Mexican territory is home
to thousands of U.S. settlers.

00:13.448 --> 00:16.149
Tensions rise as Comanche and Karankawa

00:16.151 --> 00:19.453
fight to keep their lands.

00:19.454 --> 00:21.706
Outlaws roam free,

00:21.707 --> 00:25.543
and slaves are caught in the crossfire.

00:25.544 --> 00:27.161
Mexican General Santa Anna

00:27.162 --> 00:30.414
battles to reclaim the land.

00:30.415 --> 00:32.083
U.S. President Andrew Jackson

00:32.084 --> 00:34.051
is hesitant to intervene,

00:34.052 --> 00:35.635
and Texas has no choice

00:35.637 --> 00:40.174
but to declare itself
an independent nation.

00:40.175 --> 00:42.325
Outnumbered, General Sam Houston's

00:42.344 --> 00:44.011
Texas Republic Army

00:44.012 --> 00:46.496
and Steve Austin's Ranging Company

00:46.515 --> 00:49.183
are all that stand between
Santa Anna's tyranny

00:49.184 --> 00:50.684
and independence.

00:50.685 --> 00:54.087
Texas in flames; the Alamo in ashes.

00:54.089 --> 00:56.574
Pioneers, Mexicans, Tejanos,

00:56.575 --> 01:00.244
Indians, soldiers, have no choice...

01:00.245 --> 01:02.679
fight or die.

