- Viva Mexico!
- Viva!

02:55.393 --> 02:57.276
Viva mi General!

03:04.953 --> 03:06.118
Vamos! Vamos!

03:16.498 --> 03:17.498
Sister...

03:36.685 --> 03:38.352
_

03:38.353 --> 03:40.688
_

03:40.689 --> 03:43.073
They are not soldiers.

03:43.074 --> 03:45.091
These men are pirates.

04:00.675 --> 04:02.376
Prepárate!

04:11.353 --> 04:12.351
Fuego!

04:16.474 --> 04:18.024
A la derecha!

04:26.451 --> 04:28.468
Portilla!

04:50.342 --> 04:52.176
Your Excellency,

04:52.177 --> 04:54.727
we find those women hiding in the crypt.

04:54.729 --> 04:57.564
Shall I take care of them also?

04:57.565 --> 04:59.566
Brother Almonte,

04:59.567 --> 05:01.935
your opinion?

05:01.936 --> 05:04.938
Let them tell their
drunken General Houston

05:04.939 --> 05:06.940
the stories of our triumph.

05:06.941 --> 05:08.541
Excellent.

05:10.111 --> 05:12.446
Ride to General Urrea's battalion,

05:12.447 --> 05:16.283
and order him to attack
Fort Goliad without delay.

05:34.969 --> 05:36.068
Oh!

07:54.115 --> 07:56.281
Got to get your rest, Sam.

07:56.283 --> 07:57.800
You're so peaked;

07:57.818 --> 08:00.219
you look like death eating a cracker.

08:01.739 --> 08:02.954
General.

08:02.957 --> 08:04.741
Any word from the rangers?

08:04.742 --> 08:07.744
No, sir.

08:07.745 --> 08:10.747
I have an army of
untrained, undisciplined,

08:10.748 --> 08:12.464
ill-equipped men and not enough of 'em.

08:12.466 --> 08:15.467
That's why I can't sleep.

08:15.469 --> 08:17.921
You got this wound
20-some odd years ago,

08:17.922 --> 08:19.137
and it still festers?

08:19.140 --> 08:20.823
Damn it.

08:20.841 --> 08:22.825
Huh? Yes.

08:22.843 --> 08:24.993
1814... Battle of Horseshoe Bend.

08:25.012 --> 08:26.612
Musket ball.

08:28.015 --> 08:31.184
Caught a red stick arrow
in the groin there too.

08:31.185 --> 08:35.739
Thanks to the Great Spirit,
my manhood remained intact.

08:38.491 --> 08:40.659
Little chips of splintered bone

08:40.660 --> 08:43.261
still working their way out.

08:44.832 --> 08:46.831
I sent Bowie to Travis with an order

08:46.834 --> 08:50.453
to blow up the Alamo, abandon it.

08:50.454 --> 08:52.678
I can't imagine what a trial it must be

08:52.679 --> 08:54.841
to live with this.

08:54.842 --> 08:57.192
Sir, Baker and Sherman

08:57.211 --> 08:59.095
are still waiting to see you.

08:59.096 --> 09:00.713
Much obliged.

09:00.714 --> 09:03.633
"Here to be seen seeing
me" is more like it.

09:03.634 --> 09:06.803
Delegation's arrived to
say, "Attack the Mexicans."

09:06.804 --> 09:09.606
Huh, delegation!

09:09.607 --> 09:13.560
Well, by God, come in this
instant, if not sooner.

09:13.561 --> 09:17.564
There's Juan Seguín too, sir.

09:17.565 --> 09:20.733
With due regard to the urgency
of your call, gentlemen,

09:20.734 --> 09:23.719
I hope you don't mind me
answering a call of my own.

09:23.737 --> 09:28.958
General, we mean no ill regard.

09:28.959 --> 09:34.062
We're just curious to what your plan is.

09:34.081 --> 09:36.064
I sent Deaf Smith and
his rangering company

09:36.083 --> 09:39.234
to report on the Alamo situation.

09:39.253 --> 09:41.754
Until I hear back,

09:41.755 --> 09:44.557
it'd be damn stupid to fix on any plan.

09:44.558 --> 09:46.241
There's only one plan.

09:46.260 --> 09:48.094
Attack the Alamo.

09:48.095 --> 09:51.815
Mosley, I think you know
me better than to address me

09:51.816 --> 09:53.516
like I'm some dumb son of a bitch.

09:53.517 --> 09:55.101
I cannot imagine your intention

09:55.102 --> 09:58.771
is to abandon those men, sir.

09:58.772 --> 10:00.523
It's what Davy Crockett's promising

10:00.524 --> 10:01.741
to keep their spirits hopeful.

10:01.742 --> 10:04.909
Juan, how many men are we?

10:04.912 --> 10:06.112
374...

10:06.113 --> 10:08.764
by this morning's count.

10:08.782 --> 10:11.266
What are our supplies?

10:11.285 --> 10:14.120
Two days of beans, no meat,

10:14.121 --> 10:17.773
and we're certainly short
of muskets, powder, and shot.

10:20.511 --> 10:23.213
Let me understand this.

10:23.214 --> 10:26.097
You think we ought to
attack 5,000 well-armed,

10:26.100 --> 10:30.118
well-fed Mexican veterans
supported by artillery.

10:30.137 --> 10:31.971
We do have the element of surprise, sir.

10:31.972 --> 10:33.273
Huh!

10:33.274 --> 10:36.142
It does not matter how many there are.

10:36.143 --> 10:38.895
They are only Mexicans.

10:38.896 --> 10:41.231
Juan!

10:41.232 --> 10:43.816
You're a fool, Mosley.

10:43.817 --> 10:46.969
I should let Seguín
here cut your tongue out.

10:46.987 --> 10:50.973
General, what of Colonel
Fannin's relief column?

10:50.991 --> 10:54.878
George, tell them the
status on Colonel Fannin.

10:54.879 --> 10:56.045
Our courageous colonel

10:56.046 --> 10:58.248
was on his way to the Alamo

10:58.249 --> 11:01.668
when two wagons broke
down betwixt and between.

11:01.669 --> 11:06.055
So he decided to change
course and return to Goliad.

11:06.056 --> 11:07.656
That is all the more reason

11:07.675 --> 11:10.492
we need to reinforce
Travis and Jim Bowie.

11:10.511 --> 11:13.495
Sam, what would your

11:13.514 --> 11:17.616
personal compunctions lead you to do?

11:20.237 --> 11:23.606
I will tell you what I'm not gonna do.

11:23.607 --> 11:27.076
I'm not gonna sacrifice
what little army I have

11:27.077 --> 11:29.779
by charging pell-mell
into Mexican lances.

11:29.780 --> 11:33.116
I will not fight Santa Anna
the way he wants us to fight,

11:33.117 --> 11:35.952
nor the way you think I should.

11:35.953 --> 11:37.686
Gentlemen,

11:37.705 --> 11:40.385
Texas is struggling to break free

11:40.386 --> 11:41.857
from an oppressive regime.

11:41.875 --> 11:43.092
No.

11:43.093 --> 11:44.761
We must fight for our independence

11:44.762 --> 11:46.678
like George Washington
and our forefathers

11:46.680 --> 11:49.848
fought for theirs...
with speed and mobility.

11:49.850 --> 11:51.134
Fall back.

11:51.135 --> 11:54.036
Live to fight another day.

11:54.054 --> 11:58.558
Deaf Smith and his rangers
have the right idea.

11:58.559 --> 12:00.024
As your commander,

12:00.027 --> 12:03.045
I will decide when the
day is right to do more.

12:05.115 --> 12:07.650
Now that you've been elucidated,

12:07.651 --> 12:11.821
get the hell out!

12:11.822 --> 12:13.221
General.

12:15.659 --> 12:18.760
- Juan.
- General.

12:21.832 --> 12:24.667
If it means anything,

12:24.668 --> 12:28.838
your amigos at the Alamo
call out to me in my dreams.

12:43.937 --> 12:44.937
Whoo!

12:44.938 --> 12:46.939
- Whoo-hoo!
- Whoo!

12:46.940 --> 12:48.740
You still get a buck and two bits

12:48.742 --> 12:50.526
a day working for the army?

12:50.527 --> 12:52.829
Rangers don't work for the army, Truett.

12:52.830 --> 12:54.546
We're working with the army.

12:54.548 --> 12:56.833
That's right. They don't give us orders.

12:56.834 --> 13:00.936
They offer us recommendations
and suggestions.

13:00.954 --> 13:03.285
Son, I give you a suggestion, by God,

13:03.286 --> 13:05.085
you best know it's a damn order.

13:05.086 --> 13:06.086
Sir.

13:07.956 --> 13:10.291
Hey, don't expect to get
paid anytime soon, boys.

13:10.292 --> 13:12.042
Texas ain't got no money.

13:12.043 --> 13:14.345
Least not till we run
the bean-eaters out.

13:14.346 --> 13:15.695
No offense, Flores.

13:15.697 --> 13:17.515
You's a good bean-eater.

13:17.516 --> 13:18.531
I like you.

13:23.772 --> 13:25.121
What the hell did you say?

13:29.444 --> 13:31.244
Ask him.

13:37.319 --> 13:39.252
Deaf?

13:41.156 --> 13:42.373
Deaf?

13:43.658 --> 13:45.993
What?

13:45.994 --> 13:47.661
Well, after General Houston

13:47.662 --> 13:50.047
quit being governor of Tennessee,

13:50.048 --> 13:52.550
is it true that he lit
out for the territory,

13:52.551 --> 13:54.218
took up with a Cherokee squaw,

13:54.219 --> 13:56.003
and stayed drunk for five years?

13:56.004 --> 14:00.224
I don't know he was drunk every day.

14:00.225 --> 14:03.493
Ask about his Tennessee bride.

14:03.511 --> 14:07.348
What about his tender young wife?

14:07.349 --> 14:08.682
Why'd he leave her

14:08.683 --> 14:10.568
and quit being governor?

14:10.569 --> 14:13.103
Those your words, Henry?

14:13.104 --> 14:14.271
"Tender young wife"?

14:14.272 --> 14:15.940
Ooh!

14:15.941 --> 14:17.191
That's a whole heap nicer

14:17.192 --> 14:20.176
than I would've called her.

14:20.195 --> 14:22.679
I guess she rejected him.

14:22.697 --> 14:25.366
He felt compelled to leave her...

14:25.367 --> 14:27.201
by honor, Henry.

14:27.202 --> 14:28.502
Mm-hmm.

14:28.503 --> 14:31.187
What I heard is, he
attacked her unnaturally.

14:31.206 --> 14:33.207
Now, I heard she had the organs of a man

14:33.208 --> 14:35.125
under the... oh, yeah, yeah.

14:35.126 --> 14:36.509
That's a good one.

14:36.511 --> 14:39.028
Y'all know I can't hear nothing,

14:39.047 --> 14:40.547
and I certainly can't read your lips.

14:40.548 --> 14:42.482
You're sitting all back there.

14:46.021 --> 14:48.472
Now, nobody knows what happened
between the two of them,

14:48.473 --> 14:50.689
but I do know that Sam Houston's

14:50.692 --> 14:52.542
never spoken a word against her,

14:52.560 --> 14:56.713
nor has he allowed one
spoken in his presence.

14:56.731 --> 15:00.717
What does that tell you?

15:00.735 --> 15:03.219
Reckon the same thing it tells you...

15:06.291 --> 15:09.375
That you have a grasp of things

15:09.377 --> 15:13.012
the way we can't sometimes, Erastus.

15:13.014 --> 15:14.781
Let's move out.

15:18.003 --> 15:19.385
Rest time's over, boys.

15:19.387 --> 15:20.386
Saddle up.

15:26.011 --> 15:27.393
General Sam Houston

15:27.395 --> 15:29.562
is a better man than his detractors.

15:29.564 --> 15:31.732
Then why in the hell
ain't he leading his army

15:31.733 --> 15:33.732
to help Bowie and Crockett at the Alamo?

15:33.735 --> 15:36.020
When you're half the
general he is, Elwood,

15:36.021 --> 15:37.670
maybe then I'll listen to you.

15:37.672 --> 15:39.657
It's called military tactics, Vern.

15:39.658 --> 15:41.374
That's why we're on a scout.

15:47.449 --> 15:50.284
Smoke! I seen smoke!

15:50.285 --> 15:52.385
Whoa.

15:55.507 --> 15:58.625
Over there, about 20 miles away.

15:58.626 --> 16:01.110
That's the Alamo. Deaf!

16:11.439 --> 16:14.274
That's the Alamo, boys.

16:14.275 --> 16:17.478
We lost it.

16:17.479 --> 16:19.078
Son of a bitch.

16:21.649 --> 16:23.749
God help us.

16:30.075 --> 16:31.624
Deaf.

16:40.635 --> 16:42.635
They ain't Comanches, is they?

16:42.637 --> 16:44.637
No. Karankawa.

16:44.639 --> 16:46.989
I don't know what they're
doing so far inland.

16:47.008 --> 16:48.491
Thought they was all killed off.

17:03.441 --> 17:07.027
Hell, Injuns killing
Mexicans is fine by me.

17:07.028 --> 17:09.246
So long as they ain't Comanches, right?

17:09.247 --> 17:11.448
Beans, head back.

17:11.449 --> 17:14.585
Inform General Houston
of the fate of the Alamo.

17:14.586 --> 17:16.420
Now, don't dawdle. Don't
get yourself killed.

17:16.421 --> 17:17.538
Future of Texas is at stake.

17:17.539 --> 17:19.205
- Come on.
- Yes, sir.

17:19.207 --> 17:20.540
- Ride on, Beans.
- Ride on, boy.

17:20.541 --> 17:21.708
Come on. Come on.

17:23.211 --> 17:24.545
Hee-yah! Hee-yah!

17:24.546 --> 17:28.432
Those are women in the wagon.

17:28.433 --> 17:30.217
That cuts it.

17:38.309 --> 17:39.476
Ahh!

17:39.477 --> 17:41.210
Yah!

17:54.042 --> 17:55.125
No!

17:57.128 --> 17:58.579
Mama!

18:04.586 --> 18:06.470
They got the little girl!

18:06.471 --> 18:07.711
Let's get him, Truett! Come on!

18:09.140 --> 18:11.508
We coming for you, darling!

18:14.262 --> 18:16.013
Get on that wagon, Kit!

18:50.298 --> 18:52.683
Zacharias, help the lady.

18:58.306 --> 19:00.607
I got her.

19:12.403 --> 19:14.119
I got him!

19:14.122 --> 19:15.656
Stay on him, Truett. Stay up there.

19:15.657 --> 19:16.657
I'm gaining.

19:16.658 --> 19:18.041
Stay up there.

19:18.042 --> 19:19.475
Whoo!

19:25.717 --> 19:27.251
Whoa, whoa.

19:27.252 --> 19:29.969
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

19:29.971 --> 19:31.305
Shoot him, Truett.

19:33.007 --> 19:34.657
I'm loading, damn it.

19:37.178 --> 19:38.178
All right.

19:38.179 --> 19:39.346
Take your shot. Come on.

19:39.347 --> 19:40.347
I am.

19:40.348 --> 19:41.398
Why don't you shoot him?

19:41.399 --> 19:42.933
Well, I'm trying.

19:50.575 --> 19:54.493
Oh, Yance, I got him! I got him!

19:54.495 --> 19:56.345
- You got him!
- Whoo! I got him!

19:56.364 --> 19:58.031
- You got him.
- Whoo!

19:58.032 --> 20:00.117
- Damn, nice shot.
- Hoo-hoo!

20:00.118 --> 20:01.500
Whoo!

20:01.502 --> 20:02.703
I thought we was goners, boy.

20:02.704 --> 20:04.288
I can't believe I got him.

20:04.289 --> 20:06.623
Well, I would've got him if you hadn't.

20:06.624 --> 20:08.724
Take the scalp.

20:10.545 --> 20:12.262
Well, come on, Truett.

20:12.263 --> 20:15.215
It's your first kill. You earned it.

20:15.216 --> 20:17.100
I don't need no stinky Indian pelt

20:17.101 --> 20:19.102
to prove what I done here.

20:19.103 --> 20:20.387
Hush up.

20:20.388 --> 20:22.389
- Mama!
- It ain't for you.

20:22.390 --> 20:23.557
It's for the young 'UN.

20:23.558 --> 20:25.108
Mama!

20:25.109 --> 20:26.610
When she grows up,

20:26.611 --> 20:28.278
it'll be a reminder
that justice was done

20:28.279 --> 20:30.028
on the savage that killed her mama.

20:30.031 --> 20:32.199
Go.

20:32.200 --> 20:34.667
Mama!

20:40.541 --> 20:42.209
Whoo-hoo!

20:42.210 --> 20:44.211
I don't know what I like better...

20:44.212 --> 20:46.562
killing redskins or killing Mexicans.

20:46.581 --> 20:48.382
Damn it, Vern, quit your yammering.

20:48.383 --> 20:49.565
Mister?

20:52.553 --> 20:54.087
Zacharias.

20:54.088 --> 20:55.756
Did we save them?

20:55.757 --> 20:58.759
Yes.

21:01.429 --> 21:03.279
Whoa. Karnes!

21:08.102 --> 21:11.420
Zacharias took a hit.

21:11.439 --> 21:13.589
- Oh, no.
- Damn.

21:13.608 --> 21:15.424
And you forgot to duck.

21:15.443 --> 21:17.593
I did duck.

21:17.612 --> 21:21.597
This pigsticker would've
stuck me in my chest.

21:21.616 --> 21:22.598
Yeah.

21:27.288 --> 21:28.622
What's your name, darling?

21:28.623 --> 21:30.290
Susanna.

21:30.291 --> 21:31.291
Susanna what?

21:31.292 --> 21:32.292
Dickinson.

21:34.178 --> 21:35.512
He was doing his duty.

21:35.513 --> 21:38.348
He died helping me.

21:38.349 --> 21:40.449
So long, Zach.

21:42.637 --> 21:46.789
Captain, the woman with the baby,

21:46.808 --> 21:48.791
that's Almaron Dickinson's wife.

21:48.810 --> 21:52.062
Lieutenant at the Alamo.

21:52.063 --> 21:54.231
They're the only survivors.

21:54.232 --> 21:56.066
All right, everybody.

21:56.067 --> 21:58.068
We got to move out.

21:58.069 --> 22:00.619
Leave the wagons and
them Indian horses behind.

22:00.621 --> 22:01.637
What for?

22:03.458 --> 22:05.709
Comanches.

22:06.711 --> 22:07.711
Oh, shit.

22:13.217 --> 22:14.501
Take the little one.

22:14.502 --> 22:16.134
Don't let her lay eyes on her mama.

22:16.137 --> 22:18.422
Take the women and the children.

22:18.423 --> 22:21.607
I'll bury Zacharias and this lady.

22:27.432 --> 22:29.599
Save me some poon in hell, big fellow.

22:33.237 --> 22:35.689
Henry, I'm gonna ride on ahead.

22:35.690 --> 22:37.107
See you down the road.

22:37.108 --> 22:38.241
All right.

22:56.177 --> 22:57.860
Adios, amigo.

22:57.879 --> 22:59.195
Let's go, boys.

22:59.213 --> 23:00.714
We're moving on.

23:00.715 --> 23:01.882
Rest in peace, Zacharias.

23:01.883 --> 23:03.816
We'll miss you, sir.

23:08.606 --> 23:10.206
Let's go, boy.

23:32.379 --> 23:35.214
Santa Anna's taken the Alamo!

23:35.215 --> 23:37.249
The Alamo is lost!

23:37.250 --> 23:38.751
Lordy, Lordy...

23:38.752 --> 23:42.254
Santa Anna's taken the Alamo!

23:42.255 --> 23:45.925
We've lost the Alamo!
We've lost the Alamo!

23:47.477 --> 23:49.261
Santa Anna's taken the Alamo!

23:51.314 --> 23:53.482
The Alamo has fallen!

23:53.483 --> 23:56.352
Santa Anna's taken the Alamo!

